name: Total Expenditures Full-time instructional faculty
description: Salary and benefits for all full-time for-credit instructional faculty at your institution.

name: Total Full-time instructional faculty
description: Total number of full-time instructional faculty at the end of the fall term. (Include as Full-time faculty all full-time employees who teach more than 50% of the time.)

name: Total Expenditures Part-time instructional faculty
description: Total expenditures for part-time instructional faculty and adjuncts.

name: Total Part-time instructional faculty
description: Total number of part-time instructional faculty at the end of the fall term.

name: Salary and Benefits for Full-Time Faculty
description: Salary and benefits for all full-time for-credit instructional faculty at your institution.

name: Number of Full-Time Instructional Faculty
description: Total FTE Faculty will equal total instructor credit hours taught by all full-time for-credit faculty divided by 15.

name: Number of Student Credit Hours Taught by Full-Time Instructional Faculty
description: Number of student credit hours taught by all full-time for-credit instructional faculty for the fiscal year. Report the number of credit hours for a course times the number of students enrolled in the course (include students who received a grade of W). For example, a 3 credit hour course with 30 enrolled students would generate 90 student credit hours. Exclude high school students taking classes taught by high school faculty in their high schools for college credit.

name: Salary and benefits for Part-Time Faculty
description: Salaries and benefits for all part-time for-credit instructional faculty or adjuncts.

name: Number of Part-Time Instructional Faculty
description: Total FTE part-time for-credit faculty will equal total instructor credit hours taught by all part-time faculty or adjuncts divided by 15.

name: Number of Student Credit Hours Taught by Part-Time Instructional Faculty
description: Number of student credit hours taught by all part-time for-credit instructional faculty or adjuncts for the fiscal year. Report the number of credit hours for a course times the number of students enrolled in the course (include students who received a grade of W). For example, a 3 credit hour course with 30 enrolled students would generate 90 student credit hours. Exclude high school students taking classes taught by high school faculty in their high schools for college credit.

name: Salaries and Benefits for Executive Staff
description: Salary and benefits for employees who directly support the instructional function as administrators (e.g. Chief Academic Officer, Vice President of Academic Affairs, Deans, Provosts or other instructional leadership). Do not report the President's salary or benefits in this category.

name: Number of Executive Staff
description: Number of FTE executive staff who directly support the instructional function as administrators (e.g. Chief Academic Officer, Vice President of Academic Affairs, Deans, Provosts or other instructional leadership).

name: Salaries and Benefits for Clerical and Other Professional Staff
description: Salary and benefits paid from a disciplineâ€™s instructional budget for clerical and other professional employees who directly support the for-credit instructional function.

name: Number of Clerical and Other Professional Staff
description: Enter the total FTE for-credit instructional clerical and other professional support staff.  The calculation for FTE = (total number of full-time staff) + (total part-time staff hours / 2080)

name: Non-Labor Operating Costs
description: Include materials, supplies, software, computers, equipment, professional development, conferences and travel that directly support for-credit instructional activities in the operating budget.  Exclude facilities and capital costs.

name: Program Development Full Time Faculty
description: Creating and planning curriculum at the program level for full time faculty.

name: Course Development Full Time Faculty
description: Creating and planning content and learning activities at the course level for full time faculty.

name: Teaching Full Time Faculty
description: Delivering course content, managing and monitoring student assignments and classroom (physical or virtual) activities for full time faculty.

name: Tutoring Full Time Faculty
description:
Formally providing supplemental academic assistance in support of regular coursework for full time faculty.
This is also included under Student Services.

name: Advising Full Time Faculty
description:
Assisting students with activities related to their educational experience including scheduling, academic support, planning and selecting curricular pathways and career development for full time faculty.
This is also included under Student Services.

name: Academic Service Full Time Faculty
description: Serving on committees or task forces to support teaching and learning for full time faculty.

name: Assessment and Grading Full Time Faculty
description: Assessing prior and current learning; developing and selecting assessment methodologies; evaluating student assignments and performance to award course credit, and contributing to broader assessment of student learning outcomes for full time faculty.

name: Professional Development Full Time Faculty
description: Includes institution activities and events, continuing education, community service, professional development activities, reading subject matter literature, writing scholarly papers, travel, professional association participation and other similar activities.

name: Program Development Part Time Faculty
description: Creating and planning curriculum at the program level for part time faculty.

name: Course Development Part Time Faculty
description: Creating and planning content and learning activities at the course level for part time faculty.

name: Teaching Part Time Faculty
description: Delivering course content, managing and monitoring student assignments and classroom (physical or virtual) activities for part time faculty.

name: Tutoring Part Time Faculty
description:
Formally providing supplemental academic assistance in support of regular coursework for part time faculty.
This is also included under Student Services.

name: Advising Part Time Faculty
description:
Assisting students with activities related to their educational experience including scheduling, academic support, planning and selecting curricular pathways and career development for part time faculty.
This is also included under Student Services.

name: Academic Service Part Time Faculty
description: Serving on committees or task forces to support teaching and learning for part time faculty.

name: Assessment and Grading Part Time Faculty
description: Assessing prior and current learning; developing and selecting assessment methodologies; evaluating student assignments and performance to award course credit, and contributing to broader assessment of student learning outcomes for part time faculty.

name: Professional Development Part Time Faculty
description: Includes institution activities and events, continuing education, community service, professional development activities, reading subject matter literature, writing scholarly papers, travel, professional association participation and other similar activities.

name: Student Credit Hours Taught by Full-Time Faculty
description: Number of student credit hours taught by all full-time for-credit instructional faculty for the fiscal year. Report the number of credit hours for a course times the number of students enrolled in the course (include students who received a grade of W). For example, a 3 credit hour course with 30 enrolled students would generate 90 student credit hours. Exclude high school students taking classes taught by high school faculty in their high schools for college credit.

name: Student Credit Hours Taught by Part-Time Faculty
description: Number of student credit hours taught by all part-time for-credit instructional faculty or adjuncts for the fiscal year. Report the number of credit hours for a course times the number of students enrolled in the course (include students who received a grade of W). For example, a 3 credit hour course with 30 enrolled students would generate 90 student credit hours. Exclude high school students taking classes taught by high school faculty in their high schools for college credit.

name: Admissions Contract

name: IPEDS Fall Enrollment
description: Full-time Credit Headcount plus Part-time Credit Headcount should equal IPEDS Enrollment.

name: Full-time Credit Headcount
description: Fall unduplicated credit enrollment

name: Part-time Credit Headcount
description: Fall unduplicated part-time credit enrollment

name: High School Student Concurrent Enrollment Headcount
description: High School Student Concurrent Enrollment - Headcount should be the percent of IPEDS Fall Headcount Enrollment that includes high school students enrolled either on campus, at their high school, or online.

name: High School Student Concurrent Enrollment - Credit Hours
description: High School Student Concurrent Enrollment - Credit Hours should be the percent of IPEDS Fall Credit Hour Enrollment that includes high school students enrolled either on campus, at their high school, or online.

name: Pell Grant Recipients
description: Pell Grant Recipients should be the percent of IPEDS Fall Headcount Enrollment who received Pell Grants.

name: Female Credit Students
description: Percentage of fall credit students that are female.

name: First-generation Students
description: First-generation Students should be the percent of fall credit students that represent the first generation of their families to attend a higher education institution.

name: Transfer Credit Hours
description:
Transfer Credit Hours should be the percent of IPEDS Fall Enrollment credit hours that includes full- and part-time students enrolled in courses that do not award career or technical certification, but do award credit that is transferable to other postsecondary institutions.

(For example, English, History, and Math would be considered transfer credit hours.)

name: Technical/Career Credit Hours
description: Technical/Career Credit Hours should be the percent of IPEDS Fall Enrollment that includes credit hours by full- and part-time students enrolled in programs that award career or technical certification that is not transferable. (For example, automotive technology credit hours, interior design credit hours, and practical nursing credit hours would be considered technical/career credit hours.)

name: Developmental Credit Hours
description: Developmental Credit Hours should be the percent of IPEDS Fall Enrollment that includes credit hours by full- and part-time students enrolled in developmental/remedial courses as defined by the institution.

name: Credit Student Median Age
description: Use number from most recent IPEDS enrollment data.

name: Native Hawaiian or other Pacific Islander
Tuition and Fees per Credit Hour
description: Use Fall 2012 data. Tuition and Fees per Credit Hour are the tuition and fees that full-time, in-district students are charged per credit hour. Use the figure reported to IPEDS. Enter per credit hour figure, not total tuition and fees. Credit Courses are courses that are eligible for Title IV federal financial aid.

name: Unrestricted Operating Revenue
description:
Use fiscal year 2012-2013 data.

Unrestricted Operating Revenue is defined by the National Association of College and University Business Officers (NACUBO) as "resources received that have no limitations or stipulations placed on them by external agencies or donors."

name: Local
description: Local tax revenue sources.

name: Fiscal Year Student Credit Hours
description: Number of for-credit student credit hours taught by all faculty for the fiscal year. This should be the number of credit hours for a course times the number of students enrolled in the course (include students who received a grade of W). For example, a 3 credit hour course with 30 enrolled students would generate 90 student credit hours. Exclude high school students taking classes taught by high school faculty in their high schools for college credit.

name: Credit Hours Taught by Full Time
description: Percentage of teaching load taught by full-time instructional faculty. Teaching load is measured by number credit hours assigned to credit sections with six or more students taught by full-time faculty at the end of the reporting term divided by the total number of student credit hours taught.  (Ex.  teaching load for a faculty member teaching 5 three-credit-hour courses would be 15 credit hours. )

name: Total Full-time Credit Hours
description: Number of credit hours taught by full-time instructional faculty where teaching load is measured by number of credit hours assigned to credit sections with six or more students taught by full-time faculty at the end of the reporting term.

name: Credit Hours Taught by Part Time
description: Percentage of teaching load taught by part-time instructional faculty. Teaching load is measured by number credit hours assigned to credit sections with six or more students taught by part-time faculty at the end of the reporting term divided by the total number of student credit hours taught.  (Ex.  teaching load for a faculty member teaching 5 three-credit-hour courses would be 15 credit hours.)

name: Total Part Time Credit Hours
description: Number of credit hours taught by part-time instructional faculty where teaching load is measured by number of credit hours assigned to credit sections with six or more students taught by full-time faculty at the end of the reporting term.

name: Credit Hours of Online Instruction
description: Courses belong in this category if all of the instruction is provided online and no face-to-face classroom instruction is required.

name: Credit Hours of Face to Face Instruction
description: Courses belong in this category when all of the instruction is provided in an in person physical classroom space.

name: Credit Hours of Hybrid Instruction
description: Courses that blend online and face-to-face delivery and typically have a reduced number of face to face meetings.

name: Unduplicated Headcount Full-Time, first-time in fall 2010
description: Enter unduplicated credit headcount of first-time, full-time degree- and certificate-seeking students in the fall 2010 IPEDS GRS cohort. Degree and Certificate should be as defined by the reporting institution for credit student work.

name: Number Completed Degree or Certificate Full-Time, first-time in fall 2010
description: Enter the number of students from "Unduplicated Headcount" who completed a degree or certificate before fall 2013. Students in the fall 2010 IPEDS GRS cohort who received degrees or certificates. Degree or certificate completion "trumps" transfer.

name: Number Transferred Full-Time, first-time in fall 2010
description:
Enter the number of students from "Unduplicated Headcount" who transferred to public and private four-year institutions before fall 2013.  

Please use National Student Clearinghouse data.

Degree or certificate completion "trumps" transfer. Students in the fall 2010 IPEDS GRS cohort who received degrees or certificates and then transferred to four-year institutions should be included in degree or certificate completion. Only those students who transferred but did not receive degrees or certificates should be included in "Number Transferred".

name: Unduplicated Headcount Part-Time, first-time in fall 2010
description: Enter unduplicated credit headcount of first-time, part-time degree- and certificate-seeking students in the fall 2010 IPEDS GRS cohort. Degree and Certificate should be as defined by the reporting institution for credit student work.

name: Number Completed Degree or Certificate Part-Time, first-time in fall 2010

name: Number Transferred Part-Time, first-time in fall 2010

Students in the fall 2010 IPEDS GRS cohort who received degrees or certificates and then transferred to four-year institutions should be included in degree or certificate completion. Only those students who transferred but did not receive degrees or certificates should be included in "Number Transferred".

name: Total A, B, C, P, D, F, and W Grades in Fall 2012,                                                           Credit College-level Courses
description:
Enter the total number of A, B, C, P, D, F, and W grades (or their institutional equivalents) in all credit, college-level courses at the end of the fall 2012 term for all students (include high school students earning college credits). Include laboratory grades if they are awarded independently of their associated lecture grade. Do not include incompletes, audits, and grades in developmental courses.

If your institution records + or - grades, include them in the letter grades with which they are associated (e.g. C+ grades would be reported with C grades). Map all other grades to their closest equivalent. College-level courses include courses that, if successfully completed, can be applied toward the number of courses required for achieving a degree or certificate or transferred to another institution. P grades (or your institution's equivalent) are awarded when a student takes a class for a "pass" or "fail" grade. Not all institutions may offer this option.

name: Total A, B, C, P, D, and F Grades
description: Enter the total number of A, B, C, P, D and F grades (or their institutional equivalents) in credit, college-level courses at the end of the fall 2012 term.

name: Total A, B, C, and P Grades
description: Enter the total number of A, B, C, and P grades (or their institutional equivalents) in credit, college-level courses at the end of the fall 2012 term.

name: Credit Students at the End of Fall 2012 Term
description: Enter the unduplicated number of total full- and part-time credit students (including those who withdrew from all courses) at the end of the fall 2012 term. Do not include high school students.

name: Fall 2012 Credit Students
description: Enter the total number of credit students from fall 2012 who graduated or completed certificates before the spring 2013 term.

name: Fall 2012 Credit Students Who Enrolled in Spring 2013
description: Enter the number of fall 2012 credit students who enrolled in spring 2013 term. Do not include students who graduated before spring 2013.

name: Fall 2012 Credit Students Who Graduated before Fall 2013
description: Enter the total number of credit students from fall 2012 who graduated or completed certificates before the fall 2013 term. The number should include graduates and completers from spring 2013.

name: Fall 2012 Credit Students Who Enrolled in Fall 2013
description: Enter the total number of credit students from fall 2012 who enrolled in the fall 2013 term. Do not include students who graduated before fall 2013.
